### Implementing Recharts Tooltip with Portal (Recharts v3.0)

Source: https://github.com/recharts/recharts/wiki/3.0-migration-guide

This example demonstrates how to use the new `portal` prop on the `Tooltip` component in Recharts v3.0. By providing a `portalRef`, developers can render the tooltip's DOM element into a specific external container. This allows for fine-grained control over the tooltip's positioning, styling, and z-index outside of the SVG context, addressing common layout challenges.

```jsx
const TooltipWithPortal = () => {
  const [portalRef, setPortalRef] = useState<HTMLElement | null>(null);

  return (
    <>
      <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={400}>
        <LineChart data={pageData}>
          <Line dataKey="uv" fill="green" />
          <Line dataKey="pv" fill="red" />
          {portalRef && <Tooltip portal={portalRef} wrapperStyle={{ width: '25%', marginLeft: 10 }} />}
        </LineChart>
      </ResponsiveContainer>
      <div
        ref={node => {
          if (portalRef == null && node != null) {
            setPortalRef(node);
          }
        }}
      >
        <p>Inspect the resulting HTML to see that the Tooltip element is rendered according to the portal ref.</p>
        <p>
          You now control the container the Tooltip renders in, as well as style attributes such as width, height,
          etc. Those can be managed via the Tooltip wrapperStyle prop.
        </p>
        {/* The Tooltip will render here */}
      </div>
    </>
  );
};
```

